<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <header>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0">
        <title>mocapBoston Capture Claim</title>

        <!-- Semantic UI Integration -->
        <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/semantic/semantic.min.css">
        <script
            src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.1.1.min.js"
            integrity="sha256-hVVnYaiADRTO2PzUGmuLJr8BLUSjGIZsDYGmIJLv2b8="
            crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
        <script src="/semantic/semantic.min.js"></script>
    </header>
    <body>
        <div style="background-color: #0D0A0B; padding-top: 25px; padding-bottom: 25px;">
            <div class="ui main container">
                <h1 class="ui center aligned inverted header">mocapBoston</h1>
            
                <!-- Gif Placeholder -->
                <div class="ui black inverted segment" style="max-width: 960px; margin: auto;">
                    <div style="overflow: hidden; padding-top: 56.25%; position: relative;">
                        <!-- <iframe src="https://i.giphy.com/media/jAYUbVXgESSti/source.gif" style="border: 0; height: 100%; left: 0; position: absolute; top: 0; width: 100%;" scrolling="no"></iframe> -->
                        <video autoplay loop style="border: 0; height: 100%; left: 0; position: absolute; top: 0; width: 100%;" muted preload="auto">
                            <source src="https://i.giphy.com/media/Vewuc10rHBqkXlO6fw/source.mp4" type="video/mp4">
                        </video>
                        <!-- <img src="https://i.giphy.com/media/Vewuc10rHBqkXlO6fw/source.mp4" style="border: 0; height: 100%; left: 0; position: absolute; top: 0; width: 100%;"> -->
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Session ID Segment Sample -->
                <div class="ui segment" style="width: fit-content; margin: auto; margin-top: 10px;">
                    <div class="ui mini statistic">
                        <div class="value">
                            {{id}}
                        </div>
                        <div class="label">
                            Session ID
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ui container" style="padding-top: 25px;">
            <!-- Welcome Prompt -->
            <div class="ui raised segment">
                <p>Thank you so much for participating in mocapBoston!  
                    This project is only interesting when people engage with it.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ui container" style="padding-top: 25px;">
            <div class="ui stackable three column grid">
                <div class="column">
                    <div class="ui top attached header" style="display: flex; vertical-align: middle; height: 50px;">
                        <img src="/icons/video.svg" style="float: left;">
                        <span style="margin-top: auto; margin-bottom: auto; margin-left: 10px;"><h3>
                            Privacy
                        </h3></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="ui attached green segment">
                        <p>
                            Your image and likeness is in not associated with the final capture.  
                            The cameras used as part of the capture process are driven by small computers and the recording never leaves those devices.
                            These edge computers search for markers in each image on the fly, purging each frame as soon as it has been processed.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="column">
                    <div class="ui top attached header" style="display: flex; vertical-align: middle; height: 50px;">
                        <img src="/icons/code.svg" style="float: left;">
                        <span style="margin-top: auto; margin-bottom: auto; margin-left: 10px;"><h3>
                            Data
                        </h3></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="ui attached blue segment">
                        <p>
                            Ultimatly this project is a content creation tool, generating and visualizing data from your performace.  
                            In order to serve this content to you, cloud services from Google and Giphy are utilized.
                            Your performace and it's data is anonymized and associated only with your unique session ID.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="column">
                    <div class="ui top attached header" style="display: flex; vertical-align: middle; height: 50px;">
                        <img src="/icons/share.svg" style="float: left;">
                        <span style="margin-top: auto; margin-bottom: auto; margin-left: 10px;"><h3>
                            Social
                        </h3></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="ui attached red segment">
                        <p>
                            By default your performace visualization is private, only visible to those you share it with.  
                            With your permission below, your performace will be added to the mocapBoston Gallery.  
                            Either way you will be redirected to the dedicated sharing page for your performace.
                        </p>
                        <button class="fluid ui inverted green button">Add to Gallery</button>
                        <div class="ui divider"></div>
                        <button class="fluid ui inverted red button">Keep Private</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>        


        <!-- The core Firebase JS SDK is always required and must be listed first -->
        <script src="/__/firebase/7.3.0/firebase-app.js"></script>

        <!-- TODO: Add SDKs for Firebase products that you want to use
            https://firebase.google.com/docs/web/setup#available-libraries -->
        <script src="/__/firebase/7.3.0/firebase-analytics.js"></script>

        <!-- Initialize Firebase -->
        <script src="/__/firebase/init.js"></script>
    </body>



</html>